args:
WANTED, DEAD OR ALIVE!

Alex, personal guard to the Grand Paladyn,
is hereby proclaimed WANTED for the crimes
of attempted assassination and serial murder.
Cor, lookit that poster! Cute face for\nsuch a wicked woman, 'innit?
On a more essential subject, do you know\nhow I might get to the town where\nPilika Cathedral is located?
Pilika? Sure. Yer gonna wanna make\nstraight up the northern 'ighway.
Blimey, that's a 'efty purse for one lady.\nIf only I coulds... Eh? Say, who was that\nbird what I was just talkin' to?!
Things have become quite difficult of late,\nbut I must reach the cathedral regardless.
In the former librarian's diary, one of the\nentries is about a very particular person.
In exchange for healing the librarian's\ngrandchild, this person learned how to\nobtain the key to perdition.
You are an old friend of Alex?

I sure am, sugar! See, between the time
my folks cast me out and my adoptive
parents picked me up, I lived a cold,
hard life on the streets.
That's when Alex and I became thick as...\nWell, I hate to say THIEVES, so let's just\nsay thick as sweet cream instead!
And yet, this is the first I've heard of you.\nWell enough then, Dorothy. Tell me,\nwhat brings you to me this day?

I've come bearing a request for you.
Seeing as how you once saved Alex,
I think it's the kind of thing that ONLY
you are gonna be able to pull off.
I need you to put a stop to\nAlex's quest for revenge.
I assume you refer to the attempted\nassassination and subsequent murders?

The injured parties are all connected to
the Scrolls of Perdition, yes? And I know
what the Church had poor Alex do back
in her former, uglier days.
Poor old Alex could never forgive the\nperditionists who mistreated her so.
I disagree. Alex found a new way to live,\nand swore to never again tread down\nthe path of vengeance.
Oh, honey. I'm afraid there's a former—\nand I mean VERY former—priest named\nNikolai who would disagree with that.
Are you saying she killed him?!
She was seen at his side when he died.\nFolks say he begged for his life to the\nvery end, but... Well, it didn't work out.
Oh, sweetie, I'm so sorry. Sometimes it's\nreally hard to see the evil that swims\nbeneath the surface of a girl, isn't it?
All of us have a beast inside us that\nwe do our best to keep tucked away.
Supposing for a moment that you are\ncorrect and she is plotting revenge.\nWhere would we find her now?
My adoptive Templar father had an\nidea about that, actually.
Pilika Cathedral:\n11 days after the Grissblum bombing
Strange. I was on my guard for Templars\nkeeping watch, but there's no sign of them.\nI wonder if...
I heard that you were targeting\nArchbishop Magnus yet again,\nthis time at a certain cathedral.
I don't want to involve you in this, Elly.\nGo back to the Halidom while you can.
Not until I know the truth.
It was the archbishop who was behind\nthe bombing of the prayer ceremony.\nHe plots at your assassination.
But was the attempt not made on\nArchbishop Magnus himself?
That was a ruse—he knew duty would\ncause you to sacrifice your life for his own.

And what possible motive could he have?
He was the man who sought to bring the
two sides of the Church together, so why
have me killed instead?
She is likely not even aware of the cruel\nreality to which she has been burdened.
I...I am not certain. But I AM certain that\nthe archbishop is using a former associate\nof mine—an assassin—to end your life.

He used this same assassin to frame me
for multiple crimes—and unless I miss my
guess, she is here as we speak snickering
at the situation in which I find myself.
How deplorable, Alex, that you would try\nto trick me with such a feeble tale.
Then you do not believe me?!
Only a child could believe such fancy!\nYour hatred for the perditionists has\nclearly twisted you in both mind and soul.
I...I thought you were my friend.
Don't you see? I'm trying to protect you!
I'll not be used as a tool for your revenge!\nAnd if you do not stand down now,\nI will be forced to stop you myself.
By my honor as Grand Paladyn,\nI will see this evil ended.
I should have known you would turn\nyour weapon on me one day!

Once you decide you're in the right,
you are filled with unearned confidence!
It's just like when you abandoned me
in order to flee the Church!
Please, Alex. Stand down now.\nLet not any more sins be tallied\non your already bulging ledger.
It is YOU who must stand down,\nGrand Paladyn Elisanne.
You break my heart, Alex.\nBut in that case... Haaaah!
Go, Alex! Go before I can stay my hand\nno longer and end your life myself!
Then do it, if you can!
No... Elisanne, no! I didn't want this!
Open your eyes, Elly! Open them!\n...NOOOOOOO!
